userStories.notes:
Files:
- plugins/posthog/src/index.ts (add configSchema property and ConfigSchema import)
- plugins/posthog/package.json (add configSchema to opentabs field)

Context:
PostHog has SaaS (us.posthog.com, eu.posthog.com) and self-hosted deployments. Self-hosting is a first-class PostHog deployment option.

Current code in plugins/posthog/src/index.ts:
```
import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';
...
class PostHogPlugin extends OpenTabsPlugin {
  readonly name = 'posthog';
  readonly description = 'OpenTabs plugin for PostHog';
  override readonly displayName = 'PostHog';
  readonly urlPatterns = ['*://us.posthog.com/*', '*://eu.posthog.com/*'];
  override readonly homepage = 'https://us.posthog.com';
```

Changes:

1. In plugins/posthog/src/index.ts:
   - Change `import type { ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';` to `import type { ConfigSchema, ToolDefinition } from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk';`
   - Add after `override readonly homepage = 'https://us.posthog.com';`:
     ```
     override readonly configSchema: ConfigSchema = {
       instanceUrl: {
         type: 'url' as const,
         label: 'PostHog URL',
         description: 'The URL of your self-hosted PostHog instance (e.g., https://posthog.example.com). Leave empty to use PostHog Cloud.',
         required: false,
         placeholder: 'https://posthog.example.com',
       },
     };
     ```

2. In plugins/posthog/package.json, add to `opentabs` object:
   ```json
   "configSchema": {
     "instanceUrl": {
       "type": "url",
       "label": "PostHog URL",
       "description": "The URL of your self-hosted PostHog instance (e.g., https://posthog.example.com). Leave empty to use PostHog Cloud.",
       "required": false,
       "placeholder": "https://posthog.example.com"
     }
   }
   ```

Constraints:
- Do NOT remove or change existing urlPatterns or homepage
- Do NOT set required: true
- Do NOT modify tool files, API files, or isReady logic
